# MCP Eyes Package Version Directive

## PROJECT REFERENCES

- **NPM Package**: https://www.npmjs.com/package/mcp-eyes
- **GitHub Repository**: https://github.com/datagram1/mcp-eyes

## CRITICAL: Package Version Constraints

**ONLY TWO PACKAGE VERSIONS EXIST:**

1. **mcp-eyes** - This is the ADVANCED version with full features
2. **mcp-eyes-basic** - This is the BASIC version with essential features only

## FORBIDDEN VERSIONS (DO NOT CREATE OR REFERENCE):

- ❌ mcp-eyes-enhanced
- ❌ mcp-eyes-full  
- ❌ mcp-eyes-advanced
- ❌ mcp-eyes-simplified
- ❌ Any other version names

## PACKAGE STRUCTURE:

- **mcp-eyes**: Advanced version (main package) - includes all features
- **mcp-eyes-basic**: Basic version - essential features only

## NPX CONFIGURATION EXAMPLES:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "mcp-eyes": {
      "args": ["-y", "mcp-eyes@latest", "mcp"],
      "command": "npx"
    }
  }
}
```

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "mcp-eyes-basic": {
      "args": ["-y", "mcp-eyes@latest", "mcp-eyes-basic"],
      "command": "npx"
    }
  }
}
```

## DEVELOPMENT CONSTRAINTS:

- Never suggest creating additional package versions
- Never reference non-existent versions in documentation
- Always use only the two defined package names
- When providing examples, only use mcp-eyes or mcp-eyes-basic

## ENFORCEMENT:

This directive must be followed in all:
- Documentation updates
- Configuration examples
- README files
- Package.json modifications
- Any code or text generation

**VIOLATION OF THIS DIRECTIVE IS NOT PERMITTED**
